underlying_goal: Enable developers to login to Cloud SQL Studio using IAM authentication, including setting up the necessary GCP IAM roles, Cloud SQL IAM users, and PostgreSQL grants via Terraform
friction_detail: Claude initially planned to use Secret Manager for the postgres password, but the user interrupted and specified GitHub Actions secrets instead.
brief_summary: User wanted to enable IAM-based developer login to Cloud SQL Studio; Claude investigated the codebase, designed a multi-layer plan (GCP IAM, Cloud SQL users, PostgreSQL grants), and adapted CI configuration to the user's preference, but the session ended during planning/early implementation.
